ABUJA – President Muhammadu Buhari has expressed deep anguish over the air crash that claimed the lives of Chief of Army Staff, Lt. Gen. Ibrahim Attahiru, and other military officers, presidential media adviser, Femi Adesina, said in a statement Friday night. According to the statement, the President condoled with families of the deceased, the military, and Nigerians in general, describing them as “heroes who paid the ultimate price for peace and security in the land.” While praying that God receives the souls of the patriots, the President says the crash “is one mortal blow to our underbelly, at a time our armed forces are poised to end the security challenges facing the country.” The President pledged that the departed would not die in vain. Lt. Gen. Ibrahim Attahiru was appointed Chief of Army Staff in January this year following the resignation of the erstwhile Army Chief, Lt. Gen. Tukur Buratai, alongside other Service Chiefs. •Late Chief of Army Staff, Lt.-Gen Ibrahim Attahiru ABUJA - Did the the Chief of Army Staff (COAS), Lt. -Gen. Ibrahim Attahiru, who died today in a military plane crash in Kaduna forsee his death? The late Army Chief of Staff had in March reported to have vowed that he… In "Top Stories" Abuja - The ill fated military jet that crashed on Friday in Kaduna has top military officers in the entourage of the General Ibrahim Attahiru on board. The plane crashed close to Kaduna airport where the late Chief of Army Staff was billed to commission a project in one of… In "Top Stories" Agitator like Sunday Igboho and Asari Dokubo might have landed themselves in serious trouble. This comes after the Nigerian army chief, (COAS), Lt.-Gen. Ibrahim Attahiru said on Monday, that the army is coming for the agitators. Attahiru’s warning was delivered in Uyo at the first Commanding Officers’ Workshop 2021. Igboho… In "News"